The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Jan. 28: Shareholders of Reliance Communication voted to hive off the tower business amid reports that US firms are interested in picking up stakes in the new company, which could be valued up to $5 billion. Demerger of wireless towers and related infrastructure for transfer to Reliance Telecom Infrastructure Ltd would enhance financial flexibility and cost efficiency, Reliance Communication said. 

 New Delhi, Jan. 28: The Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) has asked the finance ministry to do away with the fringe benefit tax on infrastructure development companies, besides providing them with various other sops in the budget 2007-08 to increase investment in infrastructure. 

 Mumbai, Jan. 28: Mercator Group may invest $1 billion to expand its shipping operations and go for an initial public offering to raise up to $150 million to fund dry bulk cargo vessels.It is likely to invest upto $600 million for offshore operations. 

 Mumbai, Jan. 28: GVK has consolidated its assets in power, airport, road and mining under one company, GVK Power and Infrastructure Ltd (GVKPIL). As a result of this consolidation, Mumbai International Airport and GVK Jaipur Expressway will merge under GVKPIL.

 London, Jan. 28: Bank of Baroda (BoB) plans to further expand globally, opening branches in 10 more countries, including Canada, Australia and New Zealand.




